<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871019-0004 </DOCNO><HL> GM's Hughes Gets$766 Million in Work</HL><DD> 10/19/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> GM GMH GDAEROSPACE (ARO)DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><TEXT>   GM Hughes Electronics Corp., a unit of General Motors Corp., said it received three Defense Department contracts totaling $766 million.    GM Hughes's Hughes Aircraft Co. unit won a $495 million, five-year contract to develop night vision systems and laser range finders for the Army's M-1 tank; a $190 million contract to develop weapons-control systems for the Army's Bradley fighting vehicle; and an $81 million contract to produce more than 3,000 high frequency radios for the Army, Air Force, Navy and Marines.    Hayes International Corp., a unit of Pace Industries Inc., received an $18.8 million Air Force contract for C-130 aircraft equipment.    Units of General Dynamics Corp. were awarded Navy contracts totaling $18.5 million for F-16N aircraft support and Tomahawk cruise-missile services. </TEXT></DOC>